<div class="row medium-8 large-7 columns">
	<div class="blog-post text-center">
		<h3>In-game Meanings</h3>
		<div style="text-align: left">
			Example: you want to have an army 5x10, totally 50 units. In middle of screen, at X=100 and Y=20<br>
			C -> Columns. You should input 5<br>
			R -> Rows. You should input 10<br>
			X -> Horizontal army placement from left. You should input 100<br>
			Y -> Vertical army placement from top. You should input 20<br><br>
			
			To start the battle, click blue button "Attack".<br>
			After you have started the fight, if you want to add extra armies, click blue button "Add army".<br>
			If you want at full screen, click "Max screen". If you want to full window size, click "F11" and then "Max screen"<br>
			If you paused, you can watch frame-by-frame by clicking on "Add frame"<br>
			The third number which allways increases is frames<br>
			The fourth number is the attackers (red) unit count.<br>
			The fifth number is the defenders (blue) unit count<br>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

